name: High As A Bird - Postcard Print
description:
You can tell a Robin by their distinctive red breast. This little guy however also has a serious case of redeye. He loves sitting back and partaking in a weed-filled afternoon and I don't mean searching for worms in the dandelions, it's not even his actual birthday! In this illustration the Robin is rapping a like from Drake's 'Take Care'

This illustration is #6 in my 'British garden birds do gangsta rap' series. 

My illustration has been professionally printed onto thick, sustainably sourced, 350gsm card (Elemental Chlorine free). The card is finished with a gloss laminate on the image side, but remains unlaminated on the reverse. This postcard measures 4.13 x 5.82 inches (10.5 c 14.8 cm)

name: Flippin' The Bird - Postcard print
description:
Usually noted for their beautiful singing voices, this Thrush has instead got some anger issues brought on by listening to Celph Titled for too long. Not usually known for their angry outbursts, this little chap has been learning threats from the best of then. Egg-stealers beware! In this image, the Thrush is rapping a lyric from Celph Titled's 'Right Now'.

This illustration is #4 in my 'British Birds do Gangsta Rap' series. 

My illustration has been professionally printed onto thick, sustainably sourced, 350gsm card (Elemental Chlorine free). The card is finished with a gloss laminate on the image side, but remains unlaminated on the reverse. This postcard measures 4.13 x 5.82 inches (10.5 cm 14.8 cm)
